      <description>In a cemetery in Vienna, an equation about entropy is carved onto Ludwig Boltzmann&amp;rsquo;s tombstone. If our identity is a system, this equation explains why we need the space to be &amp;lsquo;messy&amp;rsquo; in order to keep evolving.</description>
